1
00:02:10,083 --> 00:02:13,458
[BOY] What a beautiful
girl, so elegant and free.

2
00:02:13,541 --> 00:02:17,583
So graceful and delicate. She
shines brighter than the sun.

3
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:20,375
I want to meet her.
I want to talk to her.

4
00:02:20,458 --> 00:02:23,000
[MAN] To whom are you
referring, Master?

5
00:02:23,083 --> 00:02:26,000
[BOY]
That girl, Washio.

6
00:02:26,083 --> 00:02:27,791
[WASHIO]
But, Master Masatami--

7
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:32,375
[MASATAMI] Didn't you hear me?
I said I wanted to meet her.

8
00:02:32,458 --> 00:02:33,833
[WASHIO]
Yes, Master.

9
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:37,375
Oh, that lovely girl...

10
00:02:37,458 --> 00:02:40,458
That girl is like--
She's like a thrilling,

11
00:02:40,541 --> 00:02:42,875
beautiful, white silver
fish that suddenly

12
00:02:42,958 --> 00:02:44,750
appears on my bookshelf...

13
00:02:48,291 --> 00:02:50,333
[CHIDORI]
It's so hot...

14
00:03:08,791 --> 00:03:11,958
I don't believe it!
They make me go buy the food...

15
00:03:12,041 --> 00:03:14,541
Where did everyone run off to?

16
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:16,333
--[KYOKO] Kaname! 
--Huh?

17
00:03:16,416 --> 00:03:19,333
You're so slow!
How far did you go?

18
00:03:19,416 --> 00:03:21,791
We've already gone out for
a swim and come back!

19
00:03:21,875 --> 00:03:23,291
[CHIDORI]
Wasn't that a little careless?

20
00:03:23,375 --> 00:03:25,250
[KYOKO]
All right, watermelon!

21
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:27,916
You guys left our stuff
without someone to guard it.

22
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,208
All our wallets and things
are in there, you know.

23
00:03:30,291 --> 00:03:31,916
No need to worry about that.

24
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:32,833
Huh?

25
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:35,250
Now, let's split
that watermelon!

26
00:03:35,333 --> 00:03:37,166
[SOUSUKE]
This is a classic trap.

27
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:39,333
If someone carelessly
moves the bags,

28
00:03:39,416 --> 00:03:41,916
the safety pin will pop out
and trigger a blast.

29
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,625
Any thief who had tried
to steal our bags

30
00:03:44,708 --> 00:03:46,625
would surely have
learned a harsh lesson.

31
00:03:46,708 --> 00:03:50,666
Of course. So you neglected the
fact that our wallets and bags

32
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:53,833
would also have been blown up
with this hypothetical thief.

33
00:03:53,916 --> 00:03:55,833
You're such a...

34
00:03:55,916 --> 00:03:57,666
[SOUSUKE] But if we set
the example that stealing

35
00:03:57,750 --> 00:03:59,500
will be dealt with
severely like this,

36
00:03:59,583 --> 00:04:01,875
we can also contribute to the
local anti-crime measures.

37
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:03,041
It's a small price--

38
00:04:03,125 --> 00:04:04,333
[SOUSUKE grunts]

39
00:04:04,416 --> 00:04:06,333
Stop splitting hairs, would ya?

40
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:10,166
[REN] She's not as crisp
as she usually is.

41
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,125
[SHINJI]
Even her comeback lacked bite.

42
00:04:12,208 --> 00:04:14,875
[KYOKO] Never mind that,
let's get down to business!

43
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:16,791
Now let's bust this thing open.

44
00:04:16,875 --> 00:04:18,291
Fine, Fine.

45
00:04:20,125 --> 00:04:21,791
[KYOKO]
Okay! Who's gonna start? 

46
00:04:21,875 --> 00:04:23,333
How about you, Sousuke?

47
00:04:23,416 --> 00:04:24,333
[MIZUKI laughs]

48
00:04:24,416 --> 00:04:26,000
This'll be interesting.
Go ahead!

49
00:04:26,083 --> 00:04:27,375
What do I do?

50
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:29,041
[KYOKO] You split the
watermelon open with a crack

51
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:30,166
while blindfolded!

52
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:31,583
[SOUSUKE]
That's it? That's too easy!

53
00:04:31,666 --> 00:04:32,916
[MIZUKI]
That's some big talk.

54
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,875
[KYOKO] Okay, then!
Let's get the blindfold!

55
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,291
[REN]
And spin you around.

56
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:37,708
[ALL laughing]

57
00:04:37,791 --> 00:04:40,583
[ALL] And 'round, and 'round,
and 'round, and 'round.

58
00:04:40,666 --> 00:04:43,833
[KYOKO] And 'round and 'round.
That should do it!

59
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:46,000
Okay! Now begin!

60
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:48,833
[REN]
To your left, Mr. Sagara.

61
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:50,291
All right! Good luck.

62
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:53,541
[SHINJI]
No, not that way!

63
00:04:53,625 --> 00:04:54,416
Sousuke!

64
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,875
[MIZUKI]
No, no! Let him go!

65
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:58,458
Oh, brother. They're acting
like a bunch of children.

66
00:05:00,375 --> 00:05:01,458
[CHIDORI screams]

67
00:05:01,541 --> 00:05:03,125
Hey, what's the matter with you?

68
00:05:03,208 --> 00:05:04,541
It seems like you've been down

69
00:05:04,625 --> 00:05:06,625
ever since we
arrived here today.

70
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:08,083
Could it be sunstroke?

71
00:05:08,166 --> 00:05:09,500
Or perhaps something
that you've eaten?

72
00:05:09,583 --> 00:05:12,458
Uh, no, I'm fine. Honestly.

73
00:05:12,541 --> 00:05:14,666
Well, all right...
if everything's fine.

74
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:22,125
[KYOKO]
Hey, where you going?

75
00:05:22,208 --> 00:05:23,500
[SHINJI]
This way!

76
00:05:23,583 --> 00:05:25,291
[MIZUKI]
He's no good at all.

77
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:29,041
[SHINJI] Sousuke!
I told you it was this way!

78
00:05:29,125 --> 00:05:32,958
[CHIDORI] That jerk.
He didn't even say a word.

79
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:36,625
And I broke out this
new bikini and everything...

80
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:39,333
I felt pretty confident
about my looks.

81
00:05:42,458 --> 00:05:44,041
--[ALL] Huh...?
--A bullseye.

82
00:05:44,125 --> 00:05:46,000
What a simple game.

83
00:05:46,083 --> 00:05:47,833
At this level of difficulty, I--

84
