layers security,

245
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:23,333
so no normal person would be
able to sneak their way in here.

246
00:13:23,416 --> 00:13:25,458
No normal person. Right.

247
00:13:25,541 --> 00:13:27,541
[WASHIO]
Pardon me, Master Masatami.

248
00:13:27,625 --> 00:13:29,250
What is it, Washio?

249
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:31,458
[WASHIO] There are signs of
an intruder on the cliffs.

250
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:32,875
I believe it's the pervert.

251
00:13:32,958 --> 00:13:34,208
--What the--! 
--[CHIDORI] Huh?

252
00:13:34,291 --> 00:13:35,750
Who is this man?!

253
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:38,958
He's scaling the cliffs where
the security is the weakest?

254
00:13:39,041 --> 00:13:41,541
Miss Kaname, please
don't let this worry you.

255
00:13:41,625 --> 00:13:43,000
Sameshima! Hyodo!

256
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,875
[HYODO &amp; SAMESHIMA] You
called us, Master Masatami?

257
00:13:46,208 --> 00:13:47,458
[MASATAMI]
Finally!

258
00:13:47,541 --> 00:13:49,375
Miss Kanami, please
allow me to introduce them.

259
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:51,625
You already know
my driver, Washio.

260
00:13:51,708 --> 00:13:52,875
Huh?!

261
00:13:52,958 --> 00:13:54,750
[MASATAMI] The tall one
is my cook, Sameshima.

262
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:56,750
The knife he uses to
chop ingredients

263
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:59,291
he once used to chop up people.

264
00:13:59,375 --> 00:14:01,250
The other one is my
gardener, Hyodo.

265
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:02,916
He's a master of the crossbow. 

266
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,291
He can hit a target at 100
meters right between the eyes.

267
00:14:06,375 --> 00:14:09,708
Along with Washio,
they double as my bodyguards.

268
00:14:09,791 --> 00:14:12,083
All three are professional
warriors who have served

269
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:14,625
in the French Foreign Legion.

270
00:14:14,708 --> 00:14:16,125
Touché...

271
00:14:16,208 --> 00:14:17,708
Washio, Sameshima, Hyodo!

272
00:14:17,791 --> 00:14:18,583
[BODYGUARDS]
Yes!

273
00:14:18,666 --> 00:14:20,375
Eliminate the intruder at once.

274
00:14:20,458 --> 00:14:21,125
Use caution.

275
00:14:21,208 --> 00:14:22,500
[BODYGUARDS]
Master!

276
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:23,875
[CHIDORI]
Uh, wait a sec.

277
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:25,208
Actually, Masatami,

278
00:14:25,291 --> 00:14:26,750
--Actually? Actually what?
--you know, I, uh...

279
00:14:26,833 --> 00:14:28,041
I'm not sure...

280
00:14:28,125 --> 00:14:30,458
[BODYGUARDS]
Actually what?

281
00:14:30,541 --> 00:14:32,666
[CHIDORI chuckles]

282
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:33,708
Best of luck.

283
00:14:33,791 --> 00:14:35,333
Leave it to us, Miss Kaname.

284
00:14:36,708 --> 00:14:38,083
Huh? Huh?!

285
00:14:38,166 --> 00:14:39,833
[MASATAMI]
I'm surprised.

286
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:42,833
It seems Washio and the others
have taken a shine to you.

287
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:44,166
A shine?

288
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:46,500
Yes. They've always been
very curt to other guests.

289
00:14:46,583 --> 00:14:50,416
But today, it's like something
lit a fire inside them.

290
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:52,291
[CHIDORI]
And I'm pouring grease on it.

291
00:14:52,375 --> 00:14:53,708
If this is how it's gonna be,

292
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:56,083
I hope they can
drive Sousuke away...

293
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:23,416
[HYODO] Say your prayers,
you dirty freak!

294
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:24,625
Huh?

295
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:26,708
[HYODO grunts]

296
00:15:26,791 --> 00:15:28,166
[SOUSUKE]
Wait for me, Chidori.

297
00:15:30,583 --> 00:15:31,750
Please don't worry.

298
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,500
My bodyguards are the
best in the business.

299
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:35,125
[CHIDORI laughs]

300
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:36,750
Oh, yeah, Masatami!

301
00:15:36,833 --> 00:15:38,500
You mentioned that
you've been recovering

302
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:40,000
from some kind of
illness, didn't you?

303
00:15:40,083 --> 00:15:41,666
Are you still not feeling well?

304
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:43,333
[MASATAMI]
No, I'm doing fine now.

305
00:15:43,416 --> 00:15:45,875
By sick, I meant a
psychosomatic illness.

306
00:15:45,958 --> 00:15:48,541
My doctor calls it an
autonomatic imbalance.

307
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:49,875
[CHIDORI]
Oh, I've heard of that!

308
00:15:49,958 --> 00:15:52,208
It's when you get
constipated or have diarrhea

309
00:15:52,291 --> 00:15:53,458
from stress, right?

310
00:15:53,541 --> 00:15:56,583
Y-Yes. In my case, I
mainly get migraines

311
00:15:56,666 --> 00:15:57,666
and shortness of breath.

312
00:15:57,750 --> 00:15:59,958
So I can't concentrate
on my studies.

313
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:03,291
This may be too
personal a question,

314
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:06,458
but what could cause you to
get all stressed out that way?

315
00:16:06,541 --> 00:16:10,625
Uh, well, I guess I'll tell you
since it's you after all.

316
00:16:10,708 --> 00:16:12,375
Mm-hmm. Well, go for it.

317
00:16:12,458 --> 00:16:14,750
I had a cousin 6
years older than I

318
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:18,250
that I used to play with all the
time when I was really little.

319
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:20,291
She and I were in
love with each other

320
00:16:20,375 --> 00:16:22,750
and when I was 5 we vowed
that we would marry

321
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:23,833
when we got older...

322
00:16:27,083 --> 00:16:30,416
She was a sweet and
very beautiful girl...

323
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:31,958
Two months ago,
however,

324
00:16:32,041 --> 00:16:35,291
that cousin was involved
in a traffic accident.

325
00:16:35,375 --> 00:16:37,125
And your cousin died?

326
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:40,083
[MASATAMI] She got tangled
with a flower shop truck...

327
00:16:40,166 --> 00:16:42,041
And eloped with the driver!

328
00:16:42,125 --> 00:16:43,500
What?!

329
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:51,000
[SAMESHIMA laughs]

330
00:16:52,166 --> 00:16:55,041
You must be some freak if
you're able to get past Hyodo.

331
00:16:55,125 --> 00:16:57,875
Although, we'll have to see
if you can get past me.

332
00:16:57,958 --> 00:17:00,208
I will give you one word of
warning and then be silent.

333
00:17:00,291 --> 00:17:02,666
Not a single person in the
past has escaped my whip-like

334
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:03,916
slash attack with
its long reach.

335
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,500
I'm Sameshima the cook. 

336
00:17:05,583 --> 00:17:08,041
When I was a mercenary, I went
by the nickname of Sammy the S--

337
00:17:08,125 --> 00:17:09,500
[SAMESHIMA grunts]

338
00:17:11,208 --> 00:17:12,583
[SOUSUKE]
Wait for me, Chidori.

339
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:16,250
My cousin suddenly
eloped, and without me!

340
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:17,500
Uhh...

341
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:19,666
[MASATAMI] The other day,
a postcard arrived

342
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:21,208
from the Netherlands.

343
00:17:21,291 --> 00:17:24,208
It read "I'm very happy. You
should come visit us sometime."

344
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:27,375
She betrayed me and then
she had the gall to do that!

345
00:17:27,458 --> 00:17:30,958
So you're saying that's the
entire reason for your illness?

346
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:33,708
[MASATAMI]
Th-The entire reason?!

347
00:17:33,791 --> 00:17:36,750
I was betrayed by the
woman I trusted the most!

348
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:38,750
I can't trust anyone anymore!

349
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:41,250
Not if they're gonna
let me down like that!

350
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:43,791
But it was a promise
you made when you were 5.

351
00:17:43,875 --> 00:17:46,333
A promise is a promise,
no matter what age

352
00:17:46,416 --> 00:17:47,541
and she tricked me!

353
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:49,166
She cut me down to the bone!

354
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:52,458
You see? And forget this,
huh?! Forget it!

355
00:17:52,541 --> 00:17:54,625
I'm gonna cut her to pieces!

356
00:17:54,708 --> 00:17:56,333
Come on, now.

357
00:17:56,416 --> 00:17:59,208
I apologize. Whenever
I start thinking about this,

358
00:17:59,291 --> 00:18:00,666
I just get so bent out of shape.

359
00:18:00,750 --> 00:18:02,458
But I hate it when
people trick me!

360
00:18:02,541 --> 00:18:04,625
I hate it so much I could die!

361
00:18:04,708 --> 00:18:07,458
Uh, well, everybody has
things that make them mad

362
00:18:07,541 --> 00:18:08,291
just thinking about them...

363
00:18:08,375 --> 00:18:09,666
You know what I mean?

364
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:10,958
You're absolutely right.

365
00:18:11,041 --> 00:18:13,541
I just knew you'd
understand the way I feel!

366
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:16,958
Miss Kaname, you're
truly a remarkable girl.

367
00:18:17,041 --> 00:18:19,333
[CHIDORI laughs]

368
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,791
[SOUSUKE grunts]

369
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:27,958
[WASHIO] You fool.
Those sorts of projectiles

370
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:29,541
have no effect on me.

371
00:18:39,041 --> 00:18:40,541
[WASHIO]
You missed!

372
00:18:40,625 --> 00:18:42,416
[WASHIO yells]

373
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:43,041
What--

374
00:18:43,125 --> 00:18:45,208
[WASHIO screams]

375
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,875
What was that?!

376
00:18:47,958 --> 00:18:49,541
You're a formidable opponent...

377
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:51,875
You launched a grenade
knowing this would happen.

378
00:18:51,958 --> 00:18:54,708
Even calculating the
trajectory of the debris?

379
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:56,625
No, I accidentally
shot a live round

380
00:18:56,708 --> 00:18:59,083
instead of firing
a practice round.

381
00:18:59,166 --> 00:19:01,916
Damn you, you freak!

382
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,750
[SOUSUKE]
Wait for me, Chidori!

383
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:09,500
Could it be that
Washio and the others...?

384
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:11,708
[CHIDORI]
Don't tell me it didn't work.

385
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:19,041
[MASATAMI] Miss Kaname,
stay where you are,

386
00:19:19,125 --> 00:19:21,166
and even if the freak
shows up I swear--

387
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:22,958
[MASATAMI screams]

388
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,083
Chidori, you ARE here.

389
00:19:29,166 --> 00:19:30,541
No, I'm not.

390
00:19:30,625 --> 00:19:32,083
Y-You sick freak!

391
00:19:32,166 --> 00:19:35,333
As long as I'm here, you won't
lay a finger on Miss Kaname!

392
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:38,750
[MASATAMI yells]

393
00:19:41,125 --> 00:19:43,291
H-How did you--?

394
00:19:43,375 --> 00:19:45,416
That weapon is good
for nothing but decoration.

395
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:48,666
If you're gonna fight, use
something like this instead.

396
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:49,375
[CHIDORI growls]

397
00:19:49,458 --> 00:19:50,833
[SOUSUKE grunts]

398
00:19:52,666 --> 00:19:54,416
[SOUSUKE]
Ch-Chidori, that hurt.

399
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:57,250
Will you just shut up
and knock it off already?!

400
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:59,250
I've had enough of
your insensitivity!

401
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,666
Hold on! I came to rescue you.

402
00:20:01,750 --> 00:20:04,041
So... you weren't
being tortured here?

403
00:20:04,125 --> 00:20:05,916
Tortured? What are
you talking about?

404
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,041
I was having tea with him!

405
00:20:07,125 --> 00:20:08,125
So you didn't have to butt in--

406
00:20:08,208 --> 00:20:10,791
Miss Kaname... Miss Kaname...

407
00:20:10,875 --> 00:20:12,583
I thought you
told me that...

408
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:15,125
that this guy was
chasing after you...

409
00:20:16,375 --> 00:20:20,416
Oh, well... I was planning to
tell you because I figured

410
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:23,416
you maybe had the
wrong idea so-so...

411
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:28,333
Yeah, I mean, I'm sorry,
he's really a friend of mine.

412
00:20:28,416 --> 00:20:32,416
So after all that, you were
just making fun of me too?

413
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:34,375
--I didn't mean to--
--But you were, weren't you?!

414
00:20:34,458 --> 00:20:36,000
While I was gearing
up to save you,

415
00:20:36,083 --> 00:20:37,541
you were secretly mocking me!

416
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:39,291
You betrayed and tricked me!

417
00:20:39,375 --> 00:20:41,458
Well, good job!
I believed you,

418
00:20:41,541 --> 00:20:43,583
but you took my
sincerity and trampl--!

419
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:46,250
[MASATAMI grunts]

420
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:47,708
[CHIDORI]
Sousuke!

421
00:20:47,791 --> 00:20:50,833
I don't know the details,
but this is your own fault.

422
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:53,125
You surrounded yourself
with incompetent subordinates

423
00:20:53,208 --> 00:20:55,166
and allowed you judgment
to be clouded.

424
00:20:55,250 --> 00:20:57,791
If this were the battlefield,
you'd be dead ten times over.

425
00:20:57,875 --> 00:20:59,333
That's not the problem!

426
00:21:00,333 --> 00:21:01,375
Sousuke, wait!

427
00:21:01,458 --> 00:21:03,208
[MASATAMI]
M-Miss Kaname!

428
00:21:03,291 --> 00:21:05,291
[SOUSUKE] Though, I'll admit
you had some courage

429
00:21:05,375 --> 00:21:07,291
facing me in order
to protect Chidori.

430
00:21:07,375 --> 00:21:09,250
That took some guts.

431
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:11,583
What you lack now is
the right frame of mind

432
00:21:11,666 --> 00:21:12,875
to control your emotions.

433
00:21:12,958 --> 00:21:14,916
Don't deceive.
Don't be deceived.

434
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,125
Don't show weakness,
show your spirit.

435
00:21:17,208 --> 00:21:19,041
That is all. Farewell.

436
00:21:19,125 --> 00:21:21,958
[CHIDORI] Hey, Sousuke,
you're not gonna...?

437
00:21:22,041 --> 00:21:23,416
Not a problem.

438
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:32,166
[HYODO]
Master Masatami!

439
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:33,958
[SAMESHIMA]
Master Masatami, you all right?

440
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:36,250
[WASHIO] Master Masatami,
where did that freak, go?

441
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:37,833
[MASATAMI] He took our
guest and left with her.

442
00:21:37,916 --> 00:21:39,750
[BODYGUARDS]
He took Miss Kaname?!

443
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:41,666
[MASATAMI]
Let them go.

444
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:45,500
Washio, I may very well
have been too naïve.

445
00:21:45,583 --> 00:21:46,666
[WASHIO]
What?

446
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:49,833
So, don't show weakness.
Show your spirit.

447
00:21:49,916 --> 00:21:53,375
If you don't you won't be able
to protect the woman you love.

448
00:21:53,458 --> 00:21:54,916
Now I know...

449
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,291
[CHIDORI] I should at least
send him a letter of apology.

450
00:21:57,375 --> 00:21:58,916
[SOUSUKE]
What the need to apologize.

451
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,666
[CHIDORI]
'Cause he's probably torn up.

452
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:06,458
Kids his age can get hurt really
easily... trust me, I know.

453
00:22:06,541 --> 00:22:08,625
Wasn't it like
that for you, too.

454
00:22:08,708 --> 00:22:09,625
[SOUSUKE]
I've been injured.

455
00:22:09,708 --> 00:22:11,541
[CHIDORI laughs]

456
00:22:11,625 --> 00:22:14,250
[CHIDORI] Typical Sousuke...
but when all's said and done,

457
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:16,000
you did come to rescue me...
didn't you?

458
00:22:16,083 --> 00:22:17,166
Correct.

459
00:22:17,250 --> 00:22:19,958
[CHIDORI]
So, you were worried about me?

460
00:22:20,041 --> 00:22:21,458
Of course I was.

461
00:22:23,958 --> 00:22:25,791
Sorry...

462
00:22:25,875 --> 00:22:27,958
[SOUSUKE]
As long as you're all right.

463
00:23:36,583 --> 00:23:37,666
[CHIDORI]
Come to think of it...

464
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:40,000
Why is this series
called "Fumoffu" anyway?

465
00:23:40,083 --> 00:23:42,208
[SOUSUKE] There's a very
good reason for that.

466
00:23:42,291 --> 00:23:44,708
The truth will be revealed
in the next episode.

467
00:23:44,791 --> 00:23:47,250
[CHIDORI] So that's why next
time you should tune in for:

468
00:23:47,333 --> 00:23:52,041
"The Hamburger Hill of Art" and
"Single-Minded Stakeout"!

469
00:23:52,125 --> 00:23:54,458
I bet the idiots on staff
were actually cackling

470
00:23:54,541 --> 00:23:55,791
when they picked the
name, weren't they?

471
00:23:55,875 --> 00:23:57,208
[SOUSUKE] Actually,
you're right.

472
00:23:57,291 --> 00:23:58,666
[CHIDORI] Ugh...

